<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fs</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the file system.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Number of free bytes. On success, it will be equal to the number of bytes that can still be written to the file system. Calculating the free space is a time-consuming operation, especially on SPI flash. On error, returns negative value of error codes defined in <computeroutput><ref refid="errno_8h" kindref="compound">errno.h</ref></computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Number of free bytes (&gt;= 0) on success. </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EACCES</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if ZMS is still not initialized. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EIO</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if there is a memory read/write error. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EINVAL</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if <computeroutput>fs</computeroutput> is NULL. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
